title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>The concept of <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00L0.xml"
addr="jms-00L0"
title="Isomorphic sets">isomorphism</fr:link> between two sets satisfies laws like those of an <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00L4.xml"
addr="jms-00L4"
title="Equivalence relation">equivalence relation</fr:link>. In particular:</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li>reflexivity: <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A\cong  A]]></fr:tex>;</fr:li>
 <fr:li>transitivity: <fr:tex
