display="inline"><![CDATA[S\circ  R\colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } C]]></fr:tex> in a way that generalises composition of functions. In particular, we define <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S\circ  R]]></fr:tex> to be the following subset of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A\times  C]]></fr:tex>:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[  \begin {aligned}  S\circ  R &\colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } C\\   S\circ  R &=   {\mathopen {}\left \{    {\mathopen {}\left (a,c\right )\mathclose {}}\in  A\times  C    \mid     \exists  b\in  B\mathpunct {.}    a\mathrel {R}b \land  b\mathrel {S} c   \right \}\mathclose {}}  \end {aligned} ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:backmatter></fr:tree>